  "text": "The importance of endosomes to the physiological outcomes of RTK signaling is illustrated by neurotrophin signaling to sensory nerves (Fig. 1) . Neurotrophins from innervated tissues stimulate endocytosis of TrkA in axon terminals, and endosomes convey signals to the nucleus to induce transcriptional events that promote neuronal growth. Disruption of this process enhances lysosomal degradation of TrkA, inhibits NGF-induced ERK activity in endosomes, and attenuates effects of NGF on gene expression and neurite outgrowth [CITATION_1] .",
